        <abstract> 
<p>CD has observed hundreds of primrose flowers cut off their stalks, and conjectures that this was done by birds to obtain the nectar. Asks readers of <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> in England and abroad whether primroses are subject to such destruction in their localities.</p> 
        </abstract>
